questions.question:
What will be the output of the following code?

StringJoiner sj = new StringJoiner(", ", "(", ")");
System.out.println(sj.toString());
sj.add("A").add("B");
System.out.println(sj.toString());

Consider the following code:

String[] arr = {"university", "Belgaum", "2024"};
String result = String.join("-", arr);
System.out.println(result);

What is the output and how many String objects are created in memory during this operation?

Trace the step-by-step execution of the following code and show the output at each stage:

StringJoiner sj = new StringJoiner(":", "[", "]");
sj.setEmptyValue("No Data");
System.out.println("Stage 1: " + sj);
sj.add("A");
System.out.println("Stage 2: " + sj);
sj.add("B").add("C");
System.out.println("Stage 3: " + sj);
StringJoiner sj2 = new StringJoiner("-");
sj2.add("X").add("Y");
sj.merge(sj2);
System.out.println("Stage 4: " + sj);
